when to stop working during pregnancy i am weeks pregnant and i work part time the shifts are varied from in the morning one day to late the next day i can t eat during my shift except on break and can t drink either i work on my feet all day long and we can t lean on anything i m a cashier anyways so everyday my feet are swollen from even the hour shifts and are realllllllly bad by the end of the my back also f in kills me at the end of my shifts problem being i really need this job i am doing this all on my own as long as i am working my parents will let me live with them i know sad for a year old to be living at home i imagine they would let me stay even if i wasn t but thats always been the rule this job is killing me and exhausting me i feel like i am the baby not carrying one i don t want to let anyone down but when is enough enough i don t know how much more of this i can take i come home and i eat then sleep saying i barely eat during work this can t be good oh and i have a doctors appointment on monday in which i am going to bring all of this up i just feel like i am letting everyone down and that i am being a bad mother even thinking about stopping soon this part time job ended up having me working days straight last week sounds like you need to put foot down with boss if you are afraid of what your parents will say try talking to them first and let them know how you feel let them know that as soon as you can you will get another job i'm sure they'll understand they are parents too especially your mother who had to carry you for months other than that i don't know what your state offers as far as help just do some research but definitely talk to you doctor first isn't too young you may feel like it but you'll make it i had kids by time i was ended up single parent by time i was months along with second did it without any parental help somehow though its hard alot of times you do pull through good luck and god bless Knots Landing EastEnders Similarities bet